dc_description_s: This map was distributed by the Minnesota, St. Paul, and Sault Ste. Marie Railway to advertise the opening of its new "Soo Line". It was given to urge people to relocate and open businesses in towns on the railroads' route.|Relief shown by hachures.; "Photo-lith & print. by Julius Bien, 16 & 18 Park Place, N.Y."|49 x 66 centimeters|Scale approximately 1:1,000,000|General Map Collection
